[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Bochnia mine banner.jpg"],["caption=Underground chapel in Bochnia salt mine"],["unesco=yes"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Widok układu urbanistycznego Bochni z wieży kościoła farnego.jpg"],["thumb"],["350px"],["Bochnia Market Square"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.bochnia.eu\/ Bochnia"]}]}," is one of the oldest towns in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Lesser Poland Lowland"]]}," in southern ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Poland"]]},", situated around 40 kilometres southeast of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kraków"]]},". The major attraction is the oldest functioning salt mine in Europe (since the middle of 13th century, although it's being closed now, except for the historic part still open for touristic reasons). Old town has still magic atmosphere. \n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\nThere is very good bus connection between Bochnia and nearest large cities. Bochnia is located on the highway Kraków - ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Przemyśl"]]},". Very easy to get there by bus from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kraków"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tarnów"]]}," or ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rzeszów"]]}," Airport.\n\nTrains to and from Kraków leave every hour and cost around 10 zł (depending on the kind of train).\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Bochnia_kopalnia_rzezby_1.jpg"],["thumb"],["250px"],["Salt sculptures in the mine"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Park Archeologiczny Osada VI Oracze 06.JPG"],["thumb"],["250px"],["Bochnia Settlement - Archaeological Park"]]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Salt Mine"],["alt=Kopalnia Soli"],["url=http:\/\/www.kopalniasoli.pl\/en"],["email="],["address=ul. Solna 2"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=+48 14 615 36 00"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price=Ticket to the mine is around 30zł, for a night stay 60zł (night stay inclu